#####################################################################
############# COMPARING ACCURACY OF GLM and NN Predictive Models
############# v0.1483 -- 19 March 2018
#####################################################################
#-------- Author: wj107
#-------- Email: will.johnson@gmail.com
#---------------------------------
#----------- The R scripts run some pre-designed trials on pre-selected data sets in an effort to analyze the
#----------- standard error for both GLM and NN predictive models.  The standard errors are computed across 
#----------- a number of re-sampled data sets, allowing us to view averages as a reasonable estimate for true standard error
#----------- parameter for a model.

#----------- We look for trends: which model type is more accurate?  How much so?  The results are also presented graphically.
#----------- Along with the scripts is a LaTeX document outlining the process with more detail.

#---------------------------------

#---------------v0.1483 has:
#-----------'diamonds' data set and 'gamelogs' with NBA data for training/testing models
#-----------six pre-designed trials, and a function that inputs data frame, response variable, and outputs SE estimates
#-----------creates summary graphs of the SE results, distinguishing between trial size, response variable type, and model type (GLM/NN)
#-----------options to save (w.out dimensions) or display graphs.
#-----------3 chapters of a write-up:  chap1 overview, chap2 introductions, chap3 methods & results
#-----------some basic knitr:  tex file replaced by a Rnw file.  495knit file to convert Rnw to tex.
#-----------scripts for figures in chap1 and chap2,  including flowcharts w/R grid and Gmisc packages
#-----------modularized tex write-up!  one file per chapter!

